  "prompt": "What percentage of people using Quora have ever heard of \"Google\"?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there isn't publicly available specific data detailing the exact percentage of Quora users who have heard of \"Google.\" However, considering several factors, we can make an informed estimation:\n\n1. **Global Reach of Both Platforms**:\n   - **Google**: As one of the most widely used search engines globally, Google has a presence in virtually every country and is available in numerous languages. Its services are integral to daily internet usage for billions of people.\n   - **Quora**: Quora is an international platform with users from diverse geographical regions. While it may not have the same user base size as Google, it attracts a broad audience interested in asking and answering questions on a wide range of topics.\n\n2. **Internet Penetration**:\n   - Given that both platforms operate primarily online, the overlapping demographic would consist of internet users. Since Google is often the default search engine for many and is integrated into various devices and services, awareness of Google among active internet users is exceptionally high.\n\n3. **Educational and Professional Usage**:\n   - Google is not only used for personal searches but also extensively in educational and professional settings. Quora users, who often seek knowledge and information, are likely to be familiar with Google as a primary tool for research and information retrieval.\n\n4. **Accessibility and Integration**:\n   - Google\u2019s services are deeply integrated into many aspects of digital life, including browsers, smartphones (e.g., Android devices), and other applications. This pervasive integration contributes to widespread recognition.\n\n**Estimated Percentage**:\nWhile there isn't concrete data, it's reasonable to estimate that the vast majority of Quora users\u2014likely upwards of 95-99%\u2014are aware of Google. This estimation is based on Google's extensive global presence, its role as a primary search engine, and its integration into various technologies that Quora users are likely to utilize.\n\n**Note**: For precise statistics, specific user surveys or data released by Quora would be required. If such data becomes available in the future, it would provide a more accurate picture.",
